<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="134" type="hosts and biology">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="134">Hosts and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="134">
This striking species has been reared just three times, all in 2001 and in ACG dry forest (Sector Santa Rosa), from caterpillars of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Grote" authorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Euscirrhopterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poeyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="134">Euscirrhopterus poeyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Grote (
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Noctuidae</taxonomicName>
) feeding on 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Nyctaginaceae" genus="Pisonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Centrospermae" pageId="15" pageNumber="134" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="aculeata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="134">Pisonia aculeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (
<taxonomicName genus="Nyctaginaceae" lsidName="" pageId="15" pageNumber="134" rank="genus">Nyctaginaceae</taxonomicName>
) and primary parasitized by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robineau-Desvoidy" authorityYear="1863" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Lespesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="134">Lespesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
posticaDHJ01 (
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="134" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tachinidae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
